        <h3 id="analytical-introduction">Analytical Introduction <a href="#analytical-introduction" class="anchor">ğŸ”—</a></h3>
<p>In what follows I offer two examples of how this edition can be used as a resource for literary studies. The first will investigate the essayâ€™s material conditions and the ways this materiality inflects and/or reflects its concepts. The second study will demonstrate how the encoded XML can be utilized for CLS analyses of the fluid text.</p>
<p><b>Material (A)symmetry: Art, Nature, and The Mirror</b></p>
<p>In an essay concerned with discussing, and inverting, the relationships between Originality and Imitation, Art and Natureâ€”or as phrased in a revised passage â€œArt finds her own perfection within, and not outside of, herself. She is not to be judged by any external standard of <s>perfection</s> <b>resemblance</b>. She is a veil, rather than a mirror.â€ (<a href="https://brandonhurst01.github.io/The-Decay-of-Lying-2025/#/ec/f032/f/f032/folio31_fluid/-1/g" target="_blank">f.31</a>)â€”it may come as no surprise that this mirroring, and problematizing of this mirroring, surfaces on and through the materiality of the MS as well. Indeed, I suggest, the aesthetic theory proffered in the essay, deeply concerned with the intangibility of individual subjectivity and the imagination, has, for Wilde, material foundations and implications for our understanding of the material word that are legible and reified in the material conditions of inscription.</p>
<p>It is a key contention of Vivianâ€™s â€œarticleâ€ recited in the dialogue that Art supersedes, precedes, and contains exceeds nature (see Danson, Green, Riquelme, Small, and Sussman). In Vivianâ€™s schema (and Wildeâ€™s if we take Vivian as mouthpiece), Art is not to be reduced to a mirror of nature, but rather, at its pinnacles, inverts this traditional art-nature mirror relationship. Motifs of reflection and representation, of mirroring, by art, the â€œself-consciousâ€ artist, life, and nature are both the rhetorical crux and general thesis of many of the essayâ€™s critical assertions. Moreover, as I demonstrate below, the art-nature mirror dynamic that predominates the conceptual focus of the text are reified and reflected in the material condition of the MS, tangibly mirroring or echoing the aesthetic concerns of the dialogue on the very pages they were inscribed. For example, on <a href="https://brandonhurst01.github.io/The-Decay-of-Lying-2025/#/ec/f018/f/f018/folio17_fluid/-1/g?zone=%23f055_z001">f.17</a>, Wilde wrote for Vivian:</p>
<blockquote>The public<br>imagine that,Â because they are interested<br>in their immediate surroundings,Â  Art<br><i>should</i> be interested in them also, and<br><i>should</i> take them as her subject-<br>matter. But the mere fact that they<br>are interested in these things makes<br>them unsuitable subjects forÂ Art.</blockquote>
