<p>The frequent deletions of the word â€œartâ€ suggests that for all the priority Wilde gives to art, as the essay changed, Wilde systematically eliminated references to art, many of which alter the essay for the precision of certain argumentative points. For instance, â€œart of a countryâ€ was struck for â€œculture of a country,â€ while inscribing the <i>Akron</i> MS, or when Art and Life become confused during the act of crafting the art-nature mirror dynamic discussed above. This happens twice in the MS; once on <a href="https://brandonhurst01.github.io/The-Decay-of-Lying-2025/#/ec/f035/f/f035/folio34_fluid/-1/g">f.34</a>: â€œThey knew that <s>Art</s> <b>Life</b> gains from <s>Life</s> <b>Art</b>â€ (Figure 2) and the again when Wilde explicitly invokes the relationship: â€œArt Life holds the mirror up to Art,â€ (<a href="https://brandonhurst01.github.io/The-Decay-of-Lying-2025/#/ec/f042/f/f042/folio41_fluid/-1/g">f.41</a>).</p>
