<p>However, in <i>Intentions</i>, there is a precipitous fall, about 75% of the way through the essay, thatâ€™s not present in the <i>Nineteenth Century</i> variant. This is a result of the insertion of the extensive passage deriding the Nature as a derivative of Art, and lambasting any who turn idolize Nature. the â€œdegradationâ€ that Schiff associates with part of Wildeâ€™s aesthetic principle becomes measurably apparent in the cluster of the second half of the added passage rife with â€œnegativeâ€ language, which becomes the most negative point of the second half of the essay; passages, like  â€œIt was simply a very second-rate Turner, a Turner of a bad period, with all the painter&#x27;s worst faults exaggerated and over-emphasized,â€ â€œShe produces her false RenÃ©s and her sham Vautrins, just as Nature gives us, on one day a doubtful Cuyp, and on another a more than questionable Rousseau. Still, Nature irritates one more when she does things of that kind. It seems so stupid, so obvious, so unnecessary.â€ and â€œA doubtful Cuyp is unbearableâ€ (<a href="https://brandonhurst01.github.io/The-Decay-of-Lying-2025/#/ec/f042/f/f042/folio41_fluid/-1/g">f.41</a>). This added passage typifies a tendency for revisions to increase the â€œnegativeâ€ presentation of Wildeâ€™s criticisms and to redirect/redeploy the â€œnegativeâ€ sentiments in his text. For instance, Wilde insertsâ€ replaces â€œhealthy national feelingâ€ with â€œsolemn depressing truthsâ€ (<a href="https://brandonhurst01.github.io/The-Decay-of-Lying-2025/#/ec/f026/f/f026/folio25_fluid/-1/g">f.25</a>), â€œallowedâ€ for â€œsufferedâ€ (<a href="https://brandonhurst01.github.io/The-Decay-of-Lying-2025/#/ec/f024/f/f024/folio23_fluid/-1/g">f.23</a>), â€œbadâ€ for â€œdepressingâ€ (<a href="https://brandonhurst01.github.io/The-Decay-of-Lying-2025/#/ec/f019/f/f019/folio18_fluid/-1/g">f.18</a>), â€œAfter all,â€ for â€œIt is a humiliating confessionâ€ (<a href="https://brandonhurst01.github.io/The-Decay-of-Lying-2025/